<div id="review_1159958343" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1159958343" />
    <a title="Christina Rochester" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37663458-christina-rochester"><img alt="Christina Rochester" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641028704p2/37663458.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1159958343?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christina Rochester" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christina Rochester" href="/user/show/37663458-christina-rochester">Christina Rochester</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1159958343" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10223953182234186883">The Road Home tells the story of Lev, a Ukrainian who makes the journey to England in order to make life better for his family. He sends money back, but along the way he makes multiple mistakes, and really discovers who his true friends are. <br/><br/>I felt that this was a little bit meh. Like I enjoyed the story, and could frequently tell my partner what was happening in it, but at the same time I just wasn’t captured by it. The only thing that really caught me was my feelings of dislike for Sophie. Sop</span>
  <span id="freeText10223953182234186883" style="display:none">The Road Home tells the story of Lev, a Ukrainian who makes the journey to England in order to make life better for his family. He sends money back, but along the way he makes multiple mistakes, and really discovers who his true friends are. <br /><br />I felt that this was a little bit meh. Like I enjoyed the story, and could frequently tell my partner what was happening in it, but at the same time I just wasn’t captured by it. The only thing that really caught me was my feelings of dislike for Sophie. Sophie is Lev’s main love interest in the book, and boy did I despise her. Both me and my partner worked out exactly what her game was within a few pages of her being introduced, the clues obviously being there in how she was changing Lev’s appearance to fit in with her own desires, and I couldn’t stand her. She was a cow!<br /><br /><br />I liked that Lev finally found himself a dream and managed to follow through on it though. And the menus at the care home were a right hoot! </span>
  <a data-text-id="10223953182234186883" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


