      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/4183.Rose_Tremain">About Rose Tremain</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/4183.Rose_Tremain"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1399568132p3/4183.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/4183.Rose_Tremain">Rose Tremain
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
769
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5021351271904369313">Rose Tremain&apos;s best-selling novels have won many awards, including the Baileys Women&apos;s Prize, the Whitbread Novel of the Year, the James Tait Black Memorial Prize, and the Prix Femina Etranger. <i>Restoration</i>, the first of her novels to feature Robert Merivel, was shortlisted for the Booker Prize. She lives in Norfolk and London with the biographer Richard Holmes.</span>
  <span id="freeText5021351271904369313" style="display:none">Rose Tremain's best-selling novels have won many awards, including the Baileys Women's Prize, the Whitbread Novel of the Year, the James Tait Black Memorial Prize, and the Prix Femina Etranger. <i>Restoration</i>, the first of her novels to feature Robert Merivel, was shortlisted for the Booker Prize. She lives in Norfolk and London with the biographer Richard Holmes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5021351271904369313" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
